Security Recommendations based on Audit results

Controls:
- Manage employee privileges's, should comply with "Least Privilege"
- implment plans for Disaster Recovery (regular backups of system, etc.)
- create new password requirements, stronger than what is currently used
- Seperate employee duties more, CEO should not manage DTD operations and payroll along with other things
- implment IDS
- set up a regularly reacurring back up system in case of breach
- implement schedule for monitoring and maintainance of legacy systems
- Encyrption must be used, currently everything is just saved on internal server
- Implment password management system

Compliance
- implemnt least priviledge, only relevent employees shoudl have access to payment information
- create a secure envrionment to save and process card information 
- encrypt said data
- Must create Password Managment system and stronger password requirements, standard with other companies

General Data Recs
- E.U. Data must be encrypted and kept confiedntial from irrevlant departments 
- implement classifcations for current assets

System and Organiation Controls
- Limit user access with Least privilege policies
- encrypt and keep PII and SPII private
